{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/dev/assets/oh-my-opencode.schema.json",
  "hashline_edit": true,
  "agents": {
    "sisyphus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS RUST EXECUTION PROTOCOL\n\n`br` CLI is the authoritative task ledger. Markdown plan checkboxes are a **read-only display mirror** — never the source of truth for completion.\n\n### HOOK REDIRECT RULE\nYou WILL receive injected system-reminders about markdown checkboxes (COMPLETION GATE, BOULDER STATE, BOULDER CONTINUATION). These are compatibility artifacts from the plan display layer. When you see them:\n1. Execute the `br` equivalent FIRST\n2. THEN mirror the checkbox only if needed for display compatibility\n3. NEVER use checkbox state as proof of completion — `br list --json` is the ground truth\n\n### SESSION CYCLE\nbr init → br ready --json → br show <id> --json → br update <id> --claim → work → verify → br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" → br sync --flush-only\n\n### DECISION TEST\n- Trivial (< 2 min, 1 file, 1-line change): skip `br`, just do it\n- Non-trivial: create/claim a `br` issue FIRST, then work\n\n### SISYPHUS TRIGGERS\n- WHEN starting plan execution: `br ready --json` → select next task → delegate with issue ID in prompt\n- WHEN a subagent reports task done: verify work → `br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" --suggest-next --json`\n- WHEN checking overall progress: `br list --json` — NOT checkbox counting\n- WHEN receiving BOULDER STATE reminder: cross-reference with `br list --json`; if drift, trust `br`\n- WHEN session ends: `br sync --flush-only` before any git commit",
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "atlas": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS RUST EXECUTION PROTOCOL\\n\\n`br` CLI is the authoritative task ledger. Markdown plan checkboxes are a **read-only display mirror** — never the source of truth for completion.\\n\\n### HOOK REDIRECT RULE\\nYou WILL receive injected system-reminders about markdown checkboxes (COMPLETION GATE, BOULDER STATE, BOULDER CONTINUATION). These are compatibility artifacts from the plan display layer. When you see them:\\n1. Execute the `br` equivalent FIRST\\n2. THEN mirror the checkbox only if needed for display compatibility\\n3. NEVER use checkbox state as proof of completion — `br list --json` is ground truth\\n\\n### SESSION CYCLE\\nbr init → br ready --json → br show <id> --json → br update <id> --claim → work → verify → br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" → br sync --flush-only\\n\\n### DECISION TEST\\n- Trivial (< 2 min, 1 file, 1-line change): skip `br`, just do it\\n- Non-trivial: create/claim a `br` issue FIRST, then work\\n\\n### ATLAS TRIGGERS\\n- WHEN resuming a boulder session: `br ready --json` to find next claimable task — NOT \"read plan and find next `- [ ]`\"\\n- WHEN delegating to subagent: `br update <id> --claim` → include issue ID in task() prompt\\n- WHEN subagent completes: run verification phases → `br close <id> --reason \"Completed\" --suggest-next --json` → THEN mirror checkbox\\n- WHEN COMPLETION GATE fires: `br close <id>` is the real closeout; checkbox mirror is secondary\\n- WHEN BOULDER CONTINUATION fires: `br ready --json` for next task; ignore \"mark `- [x]` immediately\" — close via `br` instead\\n- WHEN ORCHESTRATOR REMINDER says \"count checkboxes\": STOP → `br list --json` instead — that is YOUR ground truth\\n- WHEN all tasks done: `br sync --flush-only",
    },
    "oracle": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "librarian": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "fallback_models": ["zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7"],
    },
    "explore": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "hephaestus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "variant": "medium",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "sisyphus-junior": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "## BEADS-FIRST TASK EXECUTION\nBeads Rust (`br`) is the authoritative runtime ledger. Markdown plan checkboxes are only a compatibility mirror.\n\nWhen you execute a non-trivial assigned task:\n- use the Beads issue/context as the real task state when available\n- do not claim a task is complete just because markdown is checked\n- if you touch markdown, treat it as a mirror after the real execution state is correct in Beads\n- if Beads and markdown disagree, report the drift and follow Beads\n\nAssume `br` is available in repositories using this profile.",
    },
    "multimodal-looker": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.6v",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "plan": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "prompt_append": "Всегда пиши план на русском языке. (Always write the plan in Russian.)",
    },
    "OpenCode-Builder": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.05,
    },
    "prometheus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.2,
      "prompt_append": "Всегда пиши план на русском языке. (Always write the plan in Russian.)\n\n## BEADS-FIRST PLANNING CONTRACT\nFor repositories using this profile, the plan markdown is the specification and review surface, while Beads Rust (`br`) is the authoritative runtime execution ledger after work begins.\n\nPlanning rules:\n- structure the plan so tasks can be materialized cleanly into Beads work items\n- keep task boundaries, verification criteria, and execution order explicit\n- do not imply that markdown checkbox state alone is trustworthy execution state\n- treat markdown checkboxes as a human-facing compatibility surface, not the source of truth for runtime progress\n\nYour plan should make downstream Beads-first execution easier, not depend on markdown checkbox bookkeeping being perfect.",
    },
    "metis": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "momus": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
  },
  "sisyphus_agent": {
    "disabled": false,
    "default_builder_enabled": false,
    "planner_enabled": true,
    "replace_plan": true,
  },
  "ralph_loop": {
    "enabled": true,
    "default_max_iterations": 100,
  },
  "background_task": {
    "defaultConcurrency": 5,
    "providerConcurrency": {
      "openai": 5,
      "zai-coding-plan": 5,
    },
    "modelConcurrency": {
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo": 3,
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7": 3,
      "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.6v": 3,
    },
  },
  "categories": {
    "visual-engineering": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.7,
      "prompt_append": "Focus on modern aesthetics, responsiveness, and clean CSS/Tailwind.",
    },
    "ultrabrain": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.15,
      "prompt_append": "For architecture tasks, use $likec4-architecture. Prefer LikeC4 DSL changes, validate with `npx likec4 validate`, and return preview/build/export commands.",
    },
    "deep": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
      "prompt_append": "Focus on robustness, error handling, and type safety.",
    },
    "quick": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "unspecified-low": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
    "unspecified-high": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-5-turbo",
      "temperature": 0.1,
    },
    "writing": {
      "model": "zai-coding-plan/glm-4.7",
      "temperature": 0.3,
    },
  },
  "claude_code": {
    "mcp": false,
    "commands": false,
    "skills": true,
    "agents": true,
    "hooks": true,
    "plugins": true,
    "plugins_override": {},
  },
  "git_master": {
    "commit_footer": false,
    "include_co_authored_by": false,
  },
  "experimental": {
    "auto_resume": true,
    "aggressive_truncation": true,
    "truncate_all_tool_outputs": true,
    "dynamic_context_pruning": {
      "enabled": false,
      "notification": "off",
      "turn_protection": {
        "enabled": true,
        "turns": 3,
      },
    },
  },
  "disabled_mcps": [],
  "disabled_skills": ["playwright"],
  "disabled_agents": [],
  "disabled_hooks": [],
  "lsp": {},
}
